        <terms:publisher>European Union Agency for Railways</terms:publisher>
        <terms:title xml:lang="en">ERA Ontology</terms:title>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">This is the human and machine-readable Ontology governed by the European Union Agency for Railways (https://www.era.europa.eu/). It represents the concepts and relationships linked to the sectorial legal framework and the use cases under the Agency´s remit, as described in the Commission Implementing Regulation (EU) [to be updated after publication] on the common specifications for the register of railway infrastructure [to be updated after publication].


Currently, this Ontology covers the European railway infrastructure and the vehicle types authorized to operate over it. It is a semantic/browsable representation of the RINF application guide (1) and ERATV application guide (2) that were built by domain experts in the RINF and ERATV working parties.

The Ontology also includes the route book concepts described in appendix D2 &quot;Elements the infrastructure manager has to provide to the railway undertaking for the Route Book&quot; as presented in the Commission Implementing Regulation (EU) [to be updated after publication] 2019/773 of 16 May 2019 on the technical specification for interoperability relating to the operation and traffic management subsystem of the rail system within the European Union and [to be updated after publication] and the Appendix D3 [to be updated after publication].</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">ERA Ontology</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:seeAlso rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI">https://www.era.europa.eu/sites/default/files/registers/docs/iu-eratv_application_guide_for_register_2016-797_en.pdf</rdfs:seeAlso>
        <rdfs:seeAlso rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI">https://www.era.europa.eu/sites/default/files/registers/docs/rinf_application_guide_for_register_en.pdf</rdfs:seeAlso>
        <owl:priorVersion rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI">https://gitlab.com/era-europa-eu/public/interoperable-data-programme/era-ontology/era-ontology/-/releases/v3.3.0</owl:priorVersion>
        <owl:versionInfo>v3.3.1</owl:versionInfo>
        <skos:changeNote xml:lang="en">

Revision 27-05-2026:
- Minor fix of improper SRS version on property era:etcsMVersion to 7.5.1.79

Revision 18-05-2026:
- Changed era:protectionLegacySystem era:inSkosConceptScheme to http://data.europa.eu/949/concepts/train-protection-legacy-systems/TrainProtectionLegacySystems
- Integrated first version of evr and eradis extensions

Revision 12-05-2026:
- Removed rdf:type owl:FunctionalProperty from era:trainDetectionSystemSpecificCheck.
- Removed XMLName for era:maxFlangeHeight and era:maxDistConsecutiveAxle as deprecated in RINF.

Revision 24-04-2026:
- Changed rdfs:range for the era:alternativeTypeName to rdf:langString.

Revision 21-04-2026:
- Added era:Siding to the domain of era:verificationINF, era:demonstrationINF and era:minimumHorizontalRadius, and adapted the SHACL shapes accordingly.
- Added missing era:XMLName &quot;CRG_Needof555&quot; on era:usesGroup555.
- Changed rdfs:domain of era:conditionsChargingElectricEnergyStorage and era:permissionChargingElectricEnergyTractionStandstill from era:ContactLineSystem to era:PlatformEdge.

Revision 20-04-2026:
- Removed era:Siding from the domain of era:maximumContactWireHeight and adapted the SHACL shapes accordingly.

Revision 07-04-2026:
- Removed useless shape references on era:etcsDegradedSituation, era:axleSpacingExplanation, era:etcsDataCommApp and era:linesideDistanceIndicationFrequency.
- Added property mapping to ERATV legislation.

Revision 30-03-2026:
- Removed functional Property for era:contactStripMaterial ; harmonized range of era:maximumContactWireHeight to xsd:double in the ontology and adapted the SHACL shapes.

Revision 26-03-2026:
- Fixed owl:versionIRI (formerly owl:versionURI used).

Revision 18-03-2026:
- Added missing labels for prov:Activity, rdf:Bag and rdf:List.

Revision 17-03-2026:
- Removed functional property for era:frequencyBandsForDetection, update the list of SKOS
- Introduced concept scheme - DocStates (former States) and updated property era:state to refering this Concept Scheme + refering to updated shapes era-sh:DocState

Revision 16-03-2026:
- Clarified era:lineCategory as a RINF infrastructure property by removing ERATV-specific metadata.
- Introduced era:compatibleWithLineCategory for ERATV VehicleType usage.
- Updated ERATV SHACL shapes accordingly; RINF SHACL shapes remain unchanged.

Revision 14-03-2026:
- Added range rdf:List for era:hasSequence and era:includes to align with the SHACL constraints that expect a list of elements for these properties.
- Added the strict of misusage of ERA ontology into RINF SHACL shapes.

Revision 12-03-2026:
- For archaic `era:oclType`, work with list instead of Skos CS.
- Fixed `conditionsAppliedRegenerativeBraking` (1.1.1.2.2.4.1) SHACL SPARQL constraint: inverted FILTER logic so the field is required only when regenerative braking is &quot;under conditions&quot; (20) or &quot;under conditions only for emergency brake&quot; (40), and corrected concept scheme from contact-line-systems to regenerative-braking (see https://gitlab.com/era-europa-eu/public/interoperable-data-programme/era-ontology/era-ontology/-/work_items/301).
- Deprecated the parameter tenGISId (1.1.1.1.2.1.2).
- Removed the corresponding SHACL validation rules.
- Changed the range of era:gsmrConstraintsOperateOnlyInCircuitSwitch to xsd:string.
- Converted the property from owl:ObjectProperty to owl:DatatypeProperty.
- Removed the link to the SKOS concept scheme as the parameter is no longer represented as a controlled vocabulary.
- Corrected the RINF index referenced in the related SHACL validation rule.

Revision 11-03-2026:
- Clarified Special(Tunnel)Area related aspects in line with updated skos CS (Gitlab public Work Item 304)

Revision 04-03-2026 (ERATV):
- Merged classes, properties and SHACL shapes from ERATV extension branch into ERA ontology.
- Introduced era:compatibleWithLineCategory for ERATV VehicleType usage.
- Updated ERATV SHACL shapes accordingly; RINF SHACL shapes remain unchanged.

Revision 03-03-2026:
- Fixed HasPartTrackOP SPARQL constraint: replaced broken UNION/FILTER pattern with rdf:type/rdfs:subClassOf* property path for matching era:Track and its subclasses.
- Added era-op-types:140 (domestic border points) to the exclusion list in HasPartTrackOP SPARQL constraint.

Revision 27-02-2026:
- Updated domain definitions of properties with era:rinfIndex in the range 1.1.1.3.2.1–1.1.1.3.2.15 and 1.1.1.3.2.16.1–1.1.1.3.2.16.13 (excluding 1.1.1.3.2.16).
- Preserved existing owl:unionOf domain expressions and replaced occurrences of era:Track or era:RunningTrack within those unions with era:ETCS.
- Change rdfs:range of era:canonicalURI to rdfs:Resource

Revision 26-02-2026:
- Moved rdfs:label SHACL constraint to era:InfrastructureElement level, removing redundant per-subclass bindings (Bridge, LevelCrossing, SpecialArea, SpecialTunnelArea, Switch) and replacing the dedicated LinearPositioningSystem Label shape with the generic RdfsLabel shape.
- Added RINF concept era-lrs:100 &quot;None&quot; and renamed era-lrs-eratv:None prefLabel to &quot;None - eratv&quot; to disambiguate RINF and ERATV None concepts in LegacyRadioSystems.

Revision 25-02-2026:
- Restricted MaxPermittedTrainLengthApplicability SPARQL constraint to only check tracks that are part of a era:SectionOfLine (see https://gitlab.com/era-europa-eu/public/interoperable-data-programme/era-ontology/era-ontology/-/issues/285).
- Corrected URIs of referenced concept schemes from the ERA Ontology.
- Corrected URIs of referenced shapes from the ERA Ontology.
- Added missing backward relationships to ERA Ontology from shapes.

Revision 24-02-2026:
- Removed dcterms:relation to non existing era:bridgeWindRestriction.
- Fixed REGEX type error in SKOS concept scheme SPARQL constraints: wrapped IRI-typed ?concept in STR() so REGEX receives an xsd:string as required by SPARQL 1.1 (see https://gitlab.com/era-europa-eu/public/interoperable-data-programme/era-ontology/era-ontology/-/issues/276).
- Fixed SolNatureApplicability SPARQL constraint to also match tracks linked via era:hasPart (not only deprecated era:track) (see https://gitlab.com/era-europa-eu/public/interoperable-data-programme/era-ontology/era-ontology/-/issues/275).
- Fixed EddyCurrentBrakingConditionsDocumentApplicability SPARQL constraint to use concept URIs from the eddy-current-braking scheme instead of magnetic-braking (see https://gitlab.com/era-europa-eu/public/interoperable-data-programme/era-ontology/era-ontology/-/issues/273).
- Fixed NoRepeatedTrackIdsSoL SPARQL constraint: removed wrongful a era:OperationalPoint type checks, as the constraint targets era:SectionOfLine subjects (see https://gitlab.com/era-europa-eu/public/interoperable-data-programme/era-ontology/era-ontology/-/issues/270).
- Added &quot;passenger stop&quot; (era-op-types:70) to the exclusion list in HasPartTrackOP SPARQL constraint (see https://gitlab.com/era-europa-eu/public/interoperable-data-programme/era-ontology/era-ontology/-/issues/269).
- Removed owl:FunctionalProperty from era:lineReferenceTunnelStart and era:lineReferenceTunnelEnd, and removed the corresponding sh:maxCount 1 SHACL constraints, as tunnels may span multiple tracks (see https://gitlab.com/era-europa-eu/public/interoperable-data-programme/era-ontology/era-ontology/-/issues/263).

Revision 23-02-2026:
- Fixed SPARQL constraint messages: ensure ?label-like variables are always bound using COALESCE, preventing message construction failures when nolabel exists (see https://gitlab.com/era-europa-eu/public/interoperable-data-programme/era-ontology/era-ontology/-/issues/264).
- Added ?path binding to all SPARQL constraint SELECT clauses, enabling SHACL result paths to be reported in validation results (see https://gitlab.com/era-europa-eu/public/interoperable-data-programme/era-ontology/era-ontology/-/issues/265).
- Moved sh:severity from sh:SPARQLConstraint instances to sh:NodeShape definitions to comply with the SHACL specification (domain of sh:severity is sh:Shape). Created dedicated *SPARQLWarning NodeShapes for constraints with sh:Warning severity (see https://gitlab.com/era-europa-eu/public/interoperable-data-programme/era-ontology/era-ontology/-/issues/280).
- Fixed conditionsAppliedRegenerativeBraking applicability constraint to also check the conditionalRegenerativeBrake value, excluding cases where regenerative braking is not applicable or not present (see https://gitlab.com/era-europa-eu/public/interoperable-data-programme/era-ontology/era-ontology/-/issues/268).
- Fixed NoRepeatedPlatformIdsOP SPARQL constraint to correctly detect duplicate platformId values (see https://gitlab.com/era-europa-eu/public/interoperable-data-programme/era-ontology/era-ontology/-/issues/271).
- Fixed NoRepeatedSidingIds SPARQL constraint to correctly detect duplicate sidingId values (see https://gitlab.com/era-europa-eu/public/interoperable-data-programme/era-ontology/era-ontology/-/issues/272).
- Fixed HABD SPARQL constraints: added missing $this in SELECT clauses (see https://gitlab.com/era-europa-eu/public/interoperable-data-programme/era-ontology/era-ontology/-/issues/274).
- Fixed SoLTrackDirectionMaxCount SPARQL constraint to use STR() for IRI comparison in duplicate track direction filter (see https://gitlab.com/era-europa-eu/public/interoperable-data-programme/era-ontology/era-ontology/-/issues/277).
- Fixed unbound variables in SPARQL constraint SELECT clauses: bound ?uopid in ReferenceBorderPointApplicability, removed unbound ?value from NoRepeatedTrackIdsSoL, and fixed ?opLabel to ?slLabel with COALESCE in SubsidiaryLocationTypeSKOS (see https://gitlab.com/era-europa-eu/public/interoperable-data-programme/era-ontology/era-ontology/-/issues/278).

