        <terms:source rdf:resource="http://data.europa.eu/eli/reg_impl/2019/773/oj"/>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Operational point at the start of section of line (kilometres increasing from start OP to the end OP).</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="http://data.europa.eu/949/"/>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Operational point at start of section of line</rdfs:label>
        <ns1:term_status>stable</ns1:term_status>
        <skos:scopeNote xml:lang="en">Each SoL may have only one start OP, and each OP has unique OP ID within the MS. The “uniqueOPID” is defined in parameter 1.2.0.0.0.2.
Each SoL has the principal direction of the traffic defined by increasing kilometres running from the start OP to the end OP.
That is why the start OP is always located at lowest kilometre of the line within the SoL.
No validation will be performed by RINF application regarding which is the start and which the end OP. This requires IM&apos;s verification. </skos:scopeNote>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>
    


