        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Specific for the French Italian and Swedish networks.
Applicable if trackside HABD is not TSI compliant, localisation of trackside hot axle box detector.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="http://data.europa.eu/949/"/>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Railway location of trackside HABD</rdfs:label>
        <ns1:term_status>stable</ns1:term_status>
        <skos:scopeNote xml:lang="en">The location (generally the distance from the origin of the line to the point of interest) on a line is given in kilometres with decimals (precision of 0.001).

It may be also possible to provide the location of the HABD as an era:netReference property for the HABD pointing to an era:NetPointReference with (at least)era:LinearPositioningSystemCoordinate</skos:scopeNote>
    </owl:DatatypeProperty>
    


